To make a new version of repository, copy file into this folder and then rerun
the createrepo command, f.e.:

Download the package to folder {{ lyr_dir_path }}:
   # yum reinstall --downloadonly --downloaddir={{ lyr_dir_path }} vim
  or
   # yum install --downloadonly --downloaddir={{ lyr_dir_path }} vim

To create/recreate a repository's metadata:
   # createrepo {{ lyr_dir_path }}

And if search does not show the uploaded package, then manually clean the cache

   # yum clean all

Testing
   # yum install vim

   and check where it has been downloaded from (note local):

     ==============================================================
      Package         Arch      Version              Repository  Size
     ==============================================================
     Installing:
      vim-enhanced    x86_64    2:7.4.629-8.el7_9       local    1.1 M

Bypasing local repository
   # yum install --disablerepo="local" vim

Getting info about repository
   # yum repoinfo local
